        "text": "The Sign of illation is a portmanteau Sign in the sense of Lewis Caroll [3], [4] who created that concept in his poem “Jabberwocky” where one encounters a bestiary of words like “slithy” – a combination of lithe and slimy. A portmanteau is literally a coat and hat rack (also a suitcase), an object designed to hold a multiplicity of objects. Just so, a portmanteau word is a holder of two or more words, each justly truncated to fit with the truncate of the other. A modern version to contemplate is the word “smog” a combination of “smoke” and “fog”."
